medical_history.chief_complaint: Right upper quadrant pain with nausea and vomiting.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began the night prior to admission. The patient had eaten a few hours before the onset of symptoms. The pain persisted until morphine was administered in the ED. The patient had never experienced pain like this before.
medical_history.family_history: Denies family history of gastrointestinal disease.
